Remarks

Usually, there may be 2 parts of any execution: entry and exit Often, one execution can close current position and open opposite position (for example, you sell 10 against current long position of 8, and as a result you have sort position of 2). In this case sell execution must be split to sell 8 for exit and sell 2 for entry)
